# Ui Component Config

`Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig` is the component-level configuration handle for dali-ui applications before the `Dali::Ui::View` tree is built.

## Table of Contents

- [Create a Component Configuration](#create-a-component-configuration)
- [Keep Configuration in Startup Code](#keep-configuration-in-startup-code)
- [Recover the Typed Configuration Handle](#recover-the-typed-configuration-handle)
- [Generated Chain Support](#generated-chain-support)

## Create a Component Configuration

Use `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::New()` to create an initialized `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig`. In a dali-ui app, this belongs in startup code before creating app-facing `Dali::Ui::View` objects.

```cpp
#include <dali-ui-components/public-api/ui-component-config.h>

Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig CreateComponentConfig()
{
  return Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::New();
}
```

`Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig` is the component configuration type for applications using dali-ui components. Keep it separate from view construction so the configuration phase stays explicit.

```cpp
#include <dali-ui-components/public-api/ui-component-config.h>

class AppUiSetup
{
public:
  AppUiSetup()
  : componentConfig(Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::New())
  {
  }

  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig GetComponentConfig() const
  {
    return componentConfig;
  }

private:
  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig componentConfig;
};
```

## Keep Configuration in Startup Code

`Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig` is a handle type and supports normal ownership transfer in application setup helpers. The move constructor `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::UiComponentConfig(UiComponentConfig&&)` lets you pass the handle through startup objects without changing the public type.

```cpp
#include <dali-ui-components/public-api/ui-component-config.h>
#include <utility>

class StartupConfiguration
{
public:
  explicit StartupConfiguration(Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig config)
  : componentConfig(std::move(config))
  {
  }

private:
  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig componentConfig;
};

StartupConfiguration BuildStartupConfiguration()
{
  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig config = Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::New();
  return StartupConfiguration(std::move(config));
}
```

Move assignment through `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::operator=` is useful when a setup object can be rebuilt during initialization.

```cpp
#include <dali-ui-components/public-api/ui-component-config.h>
#include <utility>

class ConfigSlot
{
public:
  void Reset(Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig config)
  {
    componentConfig = std::move(config);
  }

private:
  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig componentConfig;
};

void PrepareConfigSlot(ConfigSlot& slot)
{
  slot.Reset(Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::New());
}
```

The default destructor `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::~UiComponentConfig` is sufficient for normal app code. Store the handle as a value member and let object lifetime follow the startup owner.

## Recover the Typed Configuration Handle

Use `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::DownCast()` when configuration travels through generic handle-based code and needs to be restored as a component configuration handle.

```cpp
#include <dali/public-api/object/base-handle.h>
#include <dali-ui-components/public-api/ui-component-config.h>

Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig ToComponentConfig(Dali::BaseHandle handle)
{
  return Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::DownCast(handle);
}
```

`Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::DownCast()` returns a `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig`. If the supplied handle does not refer to a component configuration object, the returned handle is uninitialized.

```cpp
#include <dali/public-api/object/base-handle.h>
#include <dali-ui-components/public-api/ui-component-config.h>

class ConfigRegistry
{
public:
  void Set(Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig config)
  {
    componentConfig = std::move(config);
  }

  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig Get() const
  {
    return componentConfig;
  }

private:
  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig componentConfig;
};

void StoreRecoveredConfig(ConfigRegistry& registry, Dali::BaseHandle handle)
{
  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig config = Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::DownCast(handle);
  registry.Set(std::move(config));
}
```

This pattern keeps the dali-ui setup boundary typed as `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig` while still allowing integration code to pass handles generically.

## Generated Chain Support

`ui-component-config.autogen.h` is part of the public generated surface for `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig`. It defines `DALI_UI_CHAIN_UICOMPONENTCONFIG_METHODS`, which expands the generated chain-method support for component configuration classes.

Application code normally includes the main public header rather than including `ui-component-config.autogen.h` directly.

```cpp
#include <dali-ui-components/public-api/ui-component-config.h>

Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig BuildConfigForViewSetup()
{
  Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig config = Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig::New();
  return config;
}
```

Use `Dali::Ui::UiComponentConfig` as the app-facing configuration handle, then build the application UI with `Dali::Ui::View` objects after startup configuration is prepared.
